The President visited Graham Road Elementary School in Falls Church, Virginia, where he had a discussion with 6th grade students along with Secretary of Education Duncan. After the discussion, the President announced plans to continue the Race to the Top program and requested $1.35 billion for it in the FY 2011 budget. The announcement also included a plan to expand Race to the Top to recognize school districts that are ready for system-wide improvement of their educational policies and practices. Graham Road Elementary School is a low-income yet high-achieving school in Fairfax County, Virginia, with a majority of African American and Latino students. The school has implemented various strategies to improve student achievement, such as rigorous assessments, teacher evaluation and professional development, and effective use of data systems. The school also has a modified calendar and offers intersession classes. Teachers at Graham Road collaborate to improve instruction and use data to match their curriculum to state standards.